# Code owners — branch protection on `main` requires a review from the matching
# owner for every PR. This is how two parallel workstreams stay in their lanes:
# a PR that touches an area auto-requests that area's owner.
#
# Most-specific match wins, so add the second developer's lane(s) BELOW the
# default once their area is agreed — then they own it and the lead is no longer
# required to review every change there (and vice-versa for shared files).

# Default: the lead owns everything not claimed below.
*                                           @iamnaii

# --- Shared / high-risk files: lead review always required ---
/apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma              @iamnaii
/apps/api/prisma/migrations/                @iamnaii
/apps/api/src/app.module.ts                 @iamnaii
/apps/api/src/modules/journal/              @iamnaii
/.github/                                   @iamnaii
/.claude/                                   @iamnaii

# --- Second developer's lane (uncomment + set path + @username when agreed) ---
# /apps/api/src/modules/<their-module>/      @second-dev
# /apps/web/src/pages/<their-area>/          @second-dev
